         <div type="translation">
            <p>Μήτηρ Θεοῦ / Βασίλειος πρωτοσπαθάριος ἐπὶ τοῦ Χρυσοτρικλίνου, κριτὴς ἐπὶ τοῦ ἱπποδρόμου καὶ τῶν Ἀνατολικῶν ὁ Ξηρός.</p>
            <p xml:lang="en">Mother of God. Basileios Xeros, imperial protospatharios epi tou chrysotriklinou, krites epi tou hippodromou and of the Anatolikoi</p>
            <p xml:lang="de">Muttergottes. Basileios Xeros, kaiserlicher protospatharios epi tou chrysotriklinou, krites epi tou hippodromou und der Anatolikoi.</p>
            <p xml:lang="el">Θεοτόκος. Βασίλειος Ξηρός, πρωτοσπαθάριος επί του Χρυσοτρικλίνου, κριτή επί του ιπποδρόμου και των Ανατολικών.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary" subtype="text">
            <p xml:lang="en">The restitution of the missing parts of the legend is based on the parallels. The name Basileios Xeros[1] is attested on many other seals, however the identification of the issuer remains uncertain. 
                </p>
            <p xml:lang="de"/>
         </div>
